&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated Neonatal Nurse who has a genuine passion for education.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate needs to be an exemplary role model with excellent communication skills and be curious and initiative about all aspects of neonatal care and nursing practices. You will be working as part of a team who strive for excellence in the standards of care we provide our patients and families.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The clinical educator’s role is new in our area, and we see the successful candidate working in collaboration with the Paediatric/Neonatal Practice Development and Senior Nursing Team to provide all levels of nursing staff with an initiative and stimulating education programme across our services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will be predominantly ward based, working alongside learners, new and more experienced staff to enhance their knowledge and skills, providing teaching &amp; training, whilst supporting staff with competency assessments. Working in partnership with individuals and the team to strengthen patient safety and enhance the patient’s experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
